Genetic Algorithms, Probabilistic Methods. 

Genetic Algorithms are present in the text as the paper discusses the use of automated design optimization methods for exhaust nozzle design. Genetic Algorithms are a type of optimization algorithm that mimics the process of natural selection to find the best solution to a problem. 

Probabilistic Methods are also present in the text as the paper discusses exploring fundamental research issues that arise in the application of automated design optimization methods to realistic engineering problems. Probabilistic Methods are used in optimization algorithms to model uncertainty and randomness in the problem being solved.
